Mucinous cystadenoma of the pancreas as a cause of acute pancreatitis. Acute pancreatitis is only rarely the first presentation of a cystic neoplasm of the pancreas. Mucinous cystadenomas have not been reported to be a cause of acute pancreatitis however, we present two cases of mucinous cystadenoma of the pancreas which have caused acute pancreatitis. Both patients (female) presented acute abdominal pain, with serum amylase elevation and ultrasound scan (US) and computed tomography (CT) evidence of moderate pancreatitis, which resolved with medical treatment